arts.ttl: Stevenage won it for the fans says delighted Alex Revell
arts.sum: "It means a lot when you win games and it's just nice to celebrate because when you win, it's a special feeling. "This game does mean a lot and we're really proud of this club and the players that we've got and how hard we work.

Jamie grabs rival win for Stevenage at Cambridge United
arts.sum: A corner from Stevenage was cleared as was a cross from Cambridge and if it hadn't been for one booking on either side, Dan Sweeney for Boro and Ryan Loft for the U's, there would have been even less statistics to note. A Jamie Reid goal just past the hour settled a strange League One game at Cambridge United in Boro's favour, 1-0.

arts.ttl: Not poor but average as Stevenage lose to Huddersfield
arts.sum: One of his better games of late even if it lacked the driving runs forward with the ball that he is so good at. The 2-1 loss for Stevenage at home to Huddersfield Town was a frustrating end to what was a pleasant day weather wise.
